5\n|-\n| 17||The Master of Time: Part Two||Jack and the Thief team-up to discover the mysteries of the secretive man known only as the \u201cMaster of Time.\u201d Is this finally the way home for our solemn samurai?<ref>[http://www.idwpublishing.com/product/samurai-jack-17/ Issue 17]: [[Samurai Jack]] - Released: February, 2015 (On [http://idwpublishing.com idwpublishing.com])</ref>||February 28, 2015\n|-\n| 18||The Fallen Four||Jack stumbles upon the site of great battle, grave-robbing witches brings back the spirits of the dead to defeat the samurai warrior!<ref>[https://desertsky.popshop.comixology.com/item/JAN150505/Samurai-Jack-18-Subscription-Var Issue 18]: [[Samurai Jack]] - Released: March, 2015 (On [http://desertsky.popshop.comixology.com desertsky.popshop.comixology.com])</ref>||March 31, 2015\n|-\n| 19||The Mad Mutts of Mystery||Jack reunites with the team of dapper archaeological dogs as they search for their canine ancestry, but the secrets they fetch will leave them howling!<ref>[http://www.atomicempire.com/issue.aspx?cover=120203& Issue 19]: [[Samurai Jack]] - Released: April, 2015 (On [http://idwpublishing.com idwpublishing.com])</ref>||April 30, 2015\n|-\n| 20||Mako the Scribe||Final Issue. A scribe named Mako has heard many strange stories of the great hero known only as 'Jack.' Mako's journey to record the truth of the samurai reveals a fascinating look at his legacy and possible future: Jack the King. Jack the General. Jack the Legend.<ref>[http://www.comicbookresources.com/?page=preview&id=20466 Issue 20]: [[Samurai Jack]] - Released: May, 2015 (On [http://comicbookresources.com comicbookresources.com])</ref>||May 31, 2015\n|}\n\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" border=\"2\" width=\"100%\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ ''Samurai Jack: Lost Worlds'' comics overview\n|-  style=\"background:#980d26; text-align:center;\"\n! style=\"width:50px;\"|Issue No.\n! style=\"width:210px;\"|Issue Title\n! style=\"width:400px;\"|Overview\n! style=\"